**Issue description** (what happened, and what was expected):

Check issue: https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/3356

The code I used there could be applied to `BaseButton` like this:

``` diff
@@ -405,7 +405,7 @@ Ref<ShortCut> BaseButton:: get_shortcut() const {

 void BaseButton::_unhandled_input(InputEvent p_event) {

-   if (!is_disabled() && is_visible() && shortcut.is_valid() && shortcut->is_shortcut(p_event)) {
+   if (!is_disabled() && is_visible() && shortcut.is_valid() && shortcut->is_shortcut(p_event) && !get_viewport()->gui_has_modal_stack()) {
        if (is_toggle_mode()) {
            set_pressed(!is_pressed());
            emit_signal("toggled",is_pressed());
```

However, this will remove the possibility to place buttons with shortcuts inside a dialog. There have to be a better way to do it.
